defaultThere certainly are a lot of ways of making European markets for some of the innovations that would be derived from this product but they do need a little bit of co-ordination with some of the outside players in the famous diagram that the co-ordination group have, and they need some commitment to think that they want to push these technologies as effective European markets. 
defaultI sometimes felt that some of the best contributions to the needs assessments were slightly 1970s, “The UK could not do this on its own”. A more proactive strategy, which is what most other main European economies have, would say, “We are really good at this. Now let us make sure everyone has to do it and pay us to do it”. 
