defaultProfessor Skeadefault: Can I declare an interest and say I am a non-exec on an investment trust that does invest in the energy area? Just as a perspective on that, I think it is the deployment mechanisms and signals that are far more important in establishing confidence than the actual levels of R&amp;D funding. I very strongly agree with my two colleagues there. The other thing that I would flag up is that it depends on which parts of the energy domain you are looking at. Confidence is much more robust in energy efficiency, infrastructure, including gas infrastructure for example, than it is in renewables, which is largely driven by a climate change agenda about which people feel less certain at the moment. So I think it depends which part of the energy domain. Energy efficiency infrastructure, smart grid, people feel very confident that that is going to go ahead; renewables deployment, a little bit less even.
