defaultAll that is a slight nervousness that beyond the grand targets, beyond the concern about energy prices, some of the deployment is beginning to look more ragged, and that if that looked tight people would have a confidence in investing in innovation. As David Clarke said, it is having a sharp vision that is the important thing. Clearly no Government or country can deliver certainty, but a sharpness of the vision and not going out of focus is the thing that is needed. Everything else spooks the investor that Jim Skea has suddenly materialised.
