defaultDavid Clarkedefault: I think it is a very fair challenge. As Jim said earlier, there are a number of work-streams inside the LCICG, one of which has been set up specifically around metrics and how we evaluate projects. We are running a pilot of that at the moment, which will run over the coming months out to the middle of this year and then we will be looking at how we roll that out more effectively. The best answer I can give to your question today is to say it is recognised as a real issue and one that we need to address, and there is a very specific project 
defaultin place across all of the members to find ways of evaluating projects in a broadly compatible way but critically to get metrics that apply in particular cases.
