defaultmeasure different projects. You have your pilot; you have the existing metrics that are being used.
defaultRob Saundersdefault: No. What I was saying is that the individual organisations obviously have metrics they use, but the metrics the Technology Strategy Board uses—because we operate across the economy, we do not have a metric on the cost of energy reduction across all of our projects because most of our projects are not to do with energy. This is a matter of trying to drive consistency across the LCICG members in projects that are in the low carbon space so that we can evaluate projects more meaningfully across the group and really understand the value that is being driven across the LCICG as a public sector as a whole.
